The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Tasmania win trial tie
                                                                                                                       7                                      Tasmania win trial tie
                      
	Darwin: Cricket Australia put their revolutionary split innings one-day concept on trial Tuesday in an experimental match ahead of a board meeting where they will decide whether or not to adopt the revolutionary format this domestic season.         
	Tasmania beat South Australia by six wickets in a match at Darwin in which each team was allocated two 20-over innings on an alternating basis.         
	Cricket Australias aiming to re-ignite interest in the traditional limited-overs game amid the booming popularity of T20.         
	Under the format, bowlers can still bowl up to a maximum 10 overs, meaning teams can include four specialist bowlers and not have to rely on part-timers to make up the other one-fifth of the allocated overs.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                 
